  <thing id="f1stLangSy" name="First Language Syntax" description="You have learned enough of the basic structure of the First Language to channel more spell energy into power word spells.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Linguistics 5 ranks.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Increase the hit point maximums in each category of effect of power word spells you cast by +10%. You also gain a +2 bonus to all Bluff, Diplomacy, and Intimidate checks made by speaking." compset="Feat" summary="Increase the hp categories of your power words by 10%" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Lore1stLan"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <exprreq message="Linguistics 5 ranks required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[#skillranks[skLinguist] >= 5]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fG1stLanSy" name="Greater First Language Syntax" description="Your mastery of the First Language significantly increases your power word spells.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: First Language Syntax, Linguistics 9 ranks.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As First Language Syntax, but the skill bonuses increase to +4 and the increase in each hit point range is now 20%. These benefits do not stack with the increases from First Language Syntax." compset="Feat" summary="Power words now gain a 20% hp increase" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Lore1stLan"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <exprreq message="First Language Sytnax required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[f1stLangSy] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Linguistics 9 ranks required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[#skillranks[skLinguist] >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fHePowerW" name="Heighten Power Word" description="You can cast power word spells as if they were a higher level.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: A heightened power word spell has a higher spell level than normal (up to a maximum of 9th level). Unlike other metamagic feats, Heighten Spell actually increases the effective level of the spell that it modifies. All effects dependent on spell level (such as the ability to penetrate a lesser globe of invulnerability) are calculated according to the heightened level.\n\nAdditionally, increasing the spell level of a power word spell increases the maximum hit points it can affect. For every level increase, the hit point maximum of each effect of the spell increases by +10.\n\nFor example, Davor is a wizard with Heighten Power Word, who casts power word burden* as a 6th level spell. When determining the hp maximum of its effect categories, its duration becomes permanent for creatures with 50 hp or less, 1d4+1 minutes for creatures with 51 to 80 hp, and 1d4+1 rounds for creatures with 81 to 140 hp. \n\nLevel Increase: The heightened spell is as difficult to prepare and cast as a spell of its effective level." compset="Feat" summary="Cast power words as higher level spells, with greater hp maximums" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Lore1stLan"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="Show Spec" abbrev="Show Spec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Metamagic" name="Metamagic" abbrev="Metamagic"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fL1stLang" name="Lore of the First Language" description="You know enough of the First Language to make yourself understood to any speaking creature.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Skill Focus (Linguistics), able to speak Abyssal, Celestial, and Infernal. \n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can make a DC 15 Linguistics check as a free action once per round to communicate a simple concept to a creature that speaks a language without sharing a language with that creature. More complex\nconcepts require a DC 20 or DC 25 Linguistics check (at the GM&#146;s discretion), and generally require a move action to express.\n\nYou can also make a DC 15 to DC 25 Linguistics check as a free action to get the general gist of the meaning of any spoken statement, regardless of what language it is in. \n\nTwo creatures that both have this feat can communicate freely with each other even if they do not share a common language, though their meaning is\nimpossible for anyone without this feat to understand without the aid of magic.\n\nYou can also cast read magic, as a spell-like ability using your total hit dice as your caster level, at will." compset="Feat" summary="You can read magic at will and make yourself understood in any language" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Lore1stLan"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <pickreq thing="lAbyssal"/>
    <pickreq thing="lInfernal"/>
    <pickreq thing="lCelestial"/>
    <exprreq message="Skill Focus (Linguistics) Required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[hero.childfound[skLinguist].tagis[Helper.SkillFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fM1stLang" name="Master of the First Language" description="You know enough of the First Language to call upon its power spontaneously when spellcasting.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Lore of the First Language, Skill Focus (Linguistics), Linguistics 3 ranks, able to speak Abyssal, Celestial, and Infernal, caster level 3.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can channel stored spell energy into power word spells you know that you haven&#146;t prepared ahead of time. If you are a preparation\nspellcaster (such as clerics and wizards) you can &#147;lose&#148; a prepared spell in order to cast any power word spell of the same level or lower. If you are a\nspontaneous spellcaster (such as a sorcerer), you can apply metamagic feats to power word spells without increasing the spell&#146;s casting time." compset="Feat" summary="Swap prepared spells for power word spells." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Lore1stLan"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <pickreq thing="lAbyssal"/>
    <pickreq thing="lCelestial"/>
    <pickreq thing="lInfernal"/>
    <exprreq message="Skill Focus (Linguistics) Required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[hero.childfound[skLinguist].tagis[Helper.SkillFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Lore of the First Language Required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fL1stLang] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Linguist 3 ranks required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[#skillranks[skLinguist] >= 3]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Caster Level 3 required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[herofield[tMastCraft].value >= 3]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSp1stLang" name="Speaker of the First Language" description="You can imbue one of the words of the First Language with some of its original power.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Lore of the First Language, Skill Focus (Linguistics), Linguistics ranks equal to triple power word level (see text), able to speak Abyssal, Celestial, and Infernal.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Select a power word spell. You must have ranks in Linguistics equal to triple the level of the spell you select. The first time you select this feat you must choose a 1st level power word spell (but see Special, below). You may use this spell once per day as a spell-like ability, using your character level as its caster level. \n\n{b}Special{b}: You may select this spell more than once. Each time you may select a power word spell one level higher than the highest level you have already selected with this feat, gaining the ability to use that spell once per day as a spell-like ability.\n\n{b}NOTE{/b} I don&apos;t know how to implement the prerequisite of triple the Power Word level nor how to apply it to a specific spell. Just enter it in the box and obey the rules!" compset="Feat" summary="You gain a power word spell as a spell-like ability">
    <usesource source="Lore1stLan"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="NeedDomain"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <pickreq thing="lCelestial"/>
    <pickreq thing="lInfernal"/>
    <pickreq thing="lAbyssal"/>
    <exprreq message="Lore of the First Language Required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fL1stLang] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Skill Focus (Linguistics) Required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[hero.childfound[skLinguist].tagis[Helper.SkillFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSplitWord" name="Split Word" description="You can divide the effect of a power word spell among multiple targets.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Lore of the First Language, Skill Focus (Linguistics), Linguistics 3 ranks, able to speak Abyssal, Celestial, and Infernal, caster level 3.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you cast a power word spell, you may divide its effect between two targets within its range. You reduce the hit point maximum of every effect category of the power word spell by 50%, and apply it separately to the hp totals of the two targets.\n\nFor example, Eliana is a sorcerer with Split Word who casts power word stun at two targets, one with 28 hp and one with 70 hp. She divides the hps of the\neffect categories of her spell by 50%, so the target with 28 hp is affected for 2d4 rounds, and the target with 70 hp is affected for 1d4 rounds." compset="Feat" summary="Divide the effect of a power word spell over two targets." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="Lore1stLan"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <pickreq thing="lCelestial"/>
    <pickreq thing="lInfernal"/>
    <pickreq thing="lAbyssal"/>
    <exprreq message="Skill Focus (Linguistics) Required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[hero.childfound[skLinguist].tagis[Helper.SkillFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Lore of the First Language Required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fL1stLang] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Linguist 3 ranks required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[#skillranks[skLinguist] >= 3]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Caster Level 3 required" iserror="no"><![CDATA[herofield[tMastCraft].value >= 3]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
